1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,000
GTM Platform - AI-Native Go-to-Market
Topcoder Challenge Walkthrough

2
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:08,000
Architecture: 3 layers
Data - Agent - API + UI

3
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:13,000
Bottom layer: SQLite data model
5 tables: accounts, contacts, opportunities, signals, icp_profiles

4
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:18,000
Every table scoped by account_id
Multi-tenancy built in - no schema change needed for a second tenant

5
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:23,000
Middle layer: ReAct agent loop (Claude Haiku)
THOUGHT / ACTION / ARGS / OBSERVATION - every step logged

6
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:28,000
Top layer: FastAPI + vanilla JS UI
Real-time agent trace viewer

7
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:33,000
2 real integrations:
Serper (Google Search) + Gmail OAuth

8
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:40,000
DATA MODEL
accounts table: domain, name, industry, icp_score

9
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:47,000
contacts: linked to account by account_id
Every query filtered by account_id - that is multi-tenancy

10
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:54,000
signals: funding rounds, product launches, hires
Captured from real search results, stored per account

11
00:00:54,000 --> 00:01:01,000
opportunities: links contact to outreach action
stage field supports follow-up sequences in iteration 2

12
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:08,000
SQLite now, PostgreSQL-compatible
One import change in models.py to scale - nothing else changes

13
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:15,000
LIVE PROSPECT LOOP
Server running at localhost:8000

14
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:22,000
System already has 2 seeded accounts:
Rippling (ICP 0.92) and Linear (ICP 0.87)

15
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:28,000
Running a fresh prospect on stripe.com
Email field empty = draft only, no send

16
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:35,000
Agent is running...
Step 1: search_news - real Serper API call hitting Google

17
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:45,000
Step 2: search_contacts - LinkedIn profiles via Serper
Real results, not mocked

18
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:55,000
Step 3: score_icp - Claude reasons about ICP fit
Score computed from keywords, titles, industries in reasoning text

19
00:01:55,000 --> 00:02:05,000
Step 4: save_contact - best contact written to SQLite
Step 5: draft_email - personalized using the actual signal found

20
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:15,000
Step 6: ANSWER - agent summarizes the full run
All steps complete

21
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:22,000
Metric cards: ICP score, contacts found, signals captured, agent steps
Agent trace below - every reasoning step visible

22
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:30,000
AGENT TRACES
Purple = THOUGHT (agent reasoning)
Blue = TOOL_CALL (action + args)
Green = OBSERVATION (real API response)

23
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:38,000
The agent thought, called search_news with company name,
got back real Serper results, then decided next step

24
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:46,000
Traces also saved as JSON to /traces/
Primary evidence for Category 1: Real AI/Agent Integration

25
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:54,000
Each entry: type, timestamp, content
TOOL_CALL has tool name + args
OBSERVATION has what came back from the real API

26
00:02:54,000 --> 00:03:02,000
Nothing mocked or hardcoded
Every agent step used real Claude Haiku
Every search result came from real Serper API

27
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:10,000
INTEGRATIONS
backbone/integrations.py - all external API calls

28
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:18,000
search_news: one Serper call
Query: "{company} news funding product launch 2025 2026"
Returns: title, link, snippet

29
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:26,000
search_contacts: Serper querying LinkedIn
"site:linkedin.com/in {domain} CEO CTO VP Head Director"

30
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:34,000
send_email: Gmail OAuth2
Loads token, builds MIMEText, posts to Gmail API
Returns message_id on success

31
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:42,000
Adding a 3rd integration (HubSpot, Slack, Salesforce):
- 1 function in integrations.py
- 1 line in agent system prompt
- 1 elif in _call_tool()
Agent code does not change.

32
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:50,000
TESTS
26 integration tests, all passing

33
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:58,000
Tests cover: data model CRUD, multi-tenancy isolation,
agent parsing, ICP scoring, tool dispatch, full loop, API endpoints

34
00:03:58,000 --> 00:04:06,000
WHAT IS NOT BUILT (iteration 1)
Multi-step sequences, reply tracking, CRM pipeline view, Slack notifications

35
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:14,000
Data model already supports iteration 2:
opportunities.stage field, signals table, extensible schema

36
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:22,000
Deliberate decisions:
- SQLite over PostgreSQL (runs on reviewer's machine, one command)
- Haiku over GPT-4 (10x cheaper, full run < $0.01)
- Vanilla JS over React (no build step, loads instantly)

37
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:30,000
github.com/0x-auth/gtm-platform
26 tests passing. 4 real agent traces. 2 live integrations.
